.START 

IMREG Inc. said it will offer holders of its Class A common stock one right for each common share held, under a rights offering designed to raise additional funds for research and testing.
The New Orleans research and development concern said each right will be exchangeable for one unit -- consisting of one Class A share and one warrant to purchase an additional Class A share at $4.35 each.
Imreg said it is offering 1.6 million units for $2.50 per unit and an additional 400,000 units, to cover overallotments, at $3.50 each.
Imreg Class A shares closed yesterday at $2.125, off 12.5 cents, in national over-the-counter trading. 

